According to Board Policy BP 2105, each year the Board will decide on how the student trustees can participate in Governing Board Meetings. 
	The Board shall consider whether to afford the student member any of the following privileges:
The privilege to make and second motions;
	The privilege to attend closed sessions, other than closed sessions on personnel or collective bargaining matters;
	The privilege to receive compensation for meeting attendance at a level of $200 or 50% of the regular Board Member compensation for any given month See BP 2725;
	The privilege to serve a term commencing on May 15;
	The privilege to cast an advisory vote although the vote shall not be included in determining the vote required to approve any measure before the Board.
